## Installation

### 1. Activate Virtual Environment

```bash
source venv/bin/activate.fish   # For Fish shell
# OR
source venv/bin/activate         # For Bash/Zsh
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Configure API Keys

Create a `.env` file in the project root with your API credentials:

```env
# Qwen API Configuration
QWEN_API_ENDPOINT=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions
QWEN_API_KEY=your_qwen_api_key_here
QWEN_MODEL=qwen/qwen-2-vl-72b-instruct

# DeepSeek API Configuration
DEEPSEEK_API_ENDPOINT=https://api.deepseek.com/v1/chat/completions
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your_deepseek_api_key_here
DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-chat
```

âš ï¸ **Important:** Replace the placeholder API keys with your actual keys!

## Running the Application

```bash
streamlit run streamlit_app.py
```

The app will open in your browser at: `http://localhost:8501`

## Usage Guide

### 1. Create Account (First Time)
- Click "Sign Up" on the login page
- Fill in your details (username, password, name, gender, grade, age)
- Click "Create Account"

### 2. Login
- Enter your username and password
- Click "Login"

### 3. Dashboard
- View your test history
- See progress graphs
- Identify strong and weak topics

### 4. Take a Test
- Click "Take New Test" in sidebar
- Upload images for 12 questions (2 per topic)
- Ensure images are clear and legible
- Click "Submit Test for AI Analysis"
- Wait for AI to process (may take a few minutes)

### 5. View Results
- Results automatically saved to dashboard
- View topic-wise scores
- Read AI feedback and recommendations

